<p>I'm looking for a way to save the Google StreetViewPanoramaView (<a href="https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/android/gms/maps/StreetViewPanoramaView" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/android/gms/maps/StreetViewPanoramaView</a>) as a bitmap.</p>  <p>I tried this:</p>  <pre><code>  public Bitmap SaveBitmapOfStreetView(View v) {          v.setDrawingCacheEnabled(true);         return v.getDrawingCache(); } </code></pre>  <p>The top image is from streetview. When I click on "Save Panorama", the bottom blank image appears as the bitmap saved but it only displays the Google logo and not the actual streetview.</p>  <p>I also tried the method below to save the bitmap but achieved the same result. Not sure why this is the case, is this a google way of protecting developers from taking screenshots of streetview?</p>  <pre><code>public Bitmap SaveBitmapOfStreetView(View v) {      Bitmap b = Bitmap.createBitmap(dm.widthPixels , dm.widthPixels/3, Bitmap.Config.ARGB_8888);     Canvas c = new Canvas(b);     v.layout(0, 0, dm.widthPixels, dm.widthPixels/3);     v.draw(c);     return b; } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/24T7p.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/24T7p.png" alt="Screenshot"></a></p>